The paper deals with redundancy checking in knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves computational complexity analysis and algorithm design, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of geographical data sets suggests a possible connection to computational geometry (cs.CG), while the focus on subalgebras and qualitative calculi suggests a possible connection to databases (cs.DB).
